<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-112-155 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 947 068</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  July 1 1991 v8 n26 p99(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Tandy expects downturn in fourth fiscal quarter. (News Digest)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Fisher, Susan E.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Tandy Corp. (Finance).andO;Ticker:    TAN.andO;Topic:     Financial ReportFourth QuarterFinancial StabilityStrategic PlanningProfitSales.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>--------------------Tandy Expects Downturn In Fourth Fiscal QuarterandM;Tandy Corp. last week reported earnings for the fourth quarter ended June 30could be less than half of the $56.9 million it reported last year because oflackluster PC sales.andM;The PC maker, which operates Radio Shack stores and GRiD Systems Centers aswell as several consumer electronics chains, reported PC sales and profitmargins were sharply below last year's levels, reflecting &quot;industrywideturmoil.&quot;andM;As a result, the Fort Worth, Texas, company last week announced plans to cutcosts by more than $50 million.andP;  Tandy also plans to shift its retailbusiness from its own private-label products to name-brand items.andM;Last month, Tandy announced plans to stock PCs from IBM, Compaq ComputerCorp. and Apple Computer Inc. in a nationwide chain of superstores.andP;  Tostart, Tandy plans to purchase two Computer City stores, a joint venturebetween Inacomp Computer Centers Inc. and Mitsubishi International Corp. Thatventure lost at least $1.15 million for the year ended July 28, 1990.andM;-- Susan E. FisherandM;</TEXT></DOC>